    <p class="text-sm text-blue-500">
      The ISC was founded in 2022, as a CSO in Bangladesh. It is established to
      promote “A society that values the dignity and freedom of lives on earth”.
      We work for the most marginalized and vulnerable people that we term as
      ‘Our Concern Folks’ in short ‘OCF’. Since its inception, ISC has done
      several activities and programs designed to sustainable improvement of the
      lives and well-being of most marginalized and vulnerable communities in
      the northern part of Bangladesh. ISC believes sustainable changes happen
      through the systemic reformation of society. This reformation is not
      possible without guaranteeing the changes in the lives of the most
      vulnerable and marginalized communities. As a development organization ISC
      focuses on the value of all lives on earth with the same dignity and
      importance, transformational change of people’s social role for social
      change, balanced interaction between humans and flora and fauna for green
      ecology, priority to native needs and knowledge inclusive sustainable
      development, develop social leaders with competency based skill for
      enterprise development, priority to indigenous, disable, gender diverse
      population and occupational minorities.
    </p>
